When a thread calls Monitor.Enter  on any object, aka reference type, it checks to see if some other thread has already
taken the conch. If it has, the thread waits. If it has not, the thread takes the conch and gets on with its work on the
shared resource. Once the thread has finished its work, it calls Monitor.Exit , releasing the conch. If another thread
was waiting, it can now take the conch and do its work. This

